news_header: Ukrainian President Zelenskyi outlines a five-point victory plan aimed at ending the war by next year, focusing on NATO membership and military strategies.
news_text: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyi has announced a five-point victory plan intended to conclude the war by next year, which includes Ukraine's military alliance with NATO, defense strategies against Russian aggression, economic growth, and post-war security. The plan also has three undisclosed components shared with future partners. Zelenskyi emphasized the importance of NATO membership and called for increased military support and the removal of missile usage restrictions against Russia. He plans to discuss the proposal at the upcoming EU summit in Brussels, with hopes of securing international investment and cooperation post-war.
